    <body>
      <head>Frieda (Friedrika) Schiff [Glässner]</head>
      <div>

        <p>Sister of <ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeannette Schenker (<hi rend="italic">née</hi>
            Schiff)</ref>, thus sister-in-law to <ref cRef="entity-000632">Heinrich Schenker</ref>
          from 1919; mother of <ref cRef="entity-008445">Hedda Glässner</ref>. </p>

        <p>Frieda was the fourth child and second daughter of <ref cRef="entity-008431">Wilhelm
            (Wolf) Schiff</ref> and <ref cRef="entity-008432">Emilie (<hi rend="italic">née</hi>
            Strasser)</ref>. Nothing is known of her childhood or education. She married <ref
            cRef="entity-008446">Theodor Glässner</ref> and the couple had a daughter, <ref
            cRef="entity-008445">Hedda</ref>, who married <ref cRef="entity-003921">Hans
            Delmonte</ref>. Frieda and <ref cRef="entity-008446">Theodor</ref> lived for a time in
            <ref cRef="entity-002589">Hamburg</ref> and later moved to <ref cRef="entity-002501"
            >Berlin</ref>. A detailed account of Frieda’s illnesses and death is given in <ref
            type="correspondence" cRef="OJ-14-10_5">OJ 14/10, [5]</ref>, April 19, 1933.</p>

        <p>Jeanette corresponded with Frieda, but no items of correspondence are known to
          survive.</p>
      </div>
